article.headline: Chicago St. 86, N.J. Tech 76
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- John Cantrell and Christian Wall each scored 23 points to lead Chicago St. to a 86-76 victory over N.J. Tech on Saturday evening. David Holston scored another 15 points for Chicago St. (10-16). The game started out at 2-2, the closest the Highlanders would ever come to the Cougars, who then led the rest of the game. With 2:34 left, Justin Garris hit a 3-pointer for N.J. Tech to narrow the game to 74-71. But Wall soon answered with a jumper, and the Cougars' lead widened again. Nesho Milosevic led with 22 points for N.J. Tech (0-27), which has yet to win a game as it nears the end of its season.
